{
  "name": "[APEX] 04 - BAS Prep Data Gathering",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## [APEX] 04 - BAS Prep Data Gathering\n\n**Purpose:** Quarterly scheduled job that pulls GST and bank reconciliation data from Xero for each active BAS client, builds a pre-BAS checklist, appends to Google Sheets tracker, and emails the responsible accountant. Does NOT lodge BAS — it prepares all data for accountant review.\n\n**Trigger:** Cron — 1st Jan, Apr, Jul, Oct at 07:00 AEST\n\n**Flow:** Fetch all active quarterly clients from Airtable → loop one client at a time → pull BAS/GST/bank rec data from Xero API → build checklist → append to Google Sheets → email accountant (ready or gaps) → optionally email client for missing items\n\n**Credentials to swap before activating:**\n- `AIRTABLE_CRED_ID` → Airtable Personal Access Token\n- `XERO_CRED_ID` → Xero OAuth2 (used on HTTP Request nodes via predefined credential)\n- `GOOGLE_SHEETS_CRED_ID` → Google Sheets OAuth2\n- `GMAIL_CRED_ID` → Gmail OAuth2\n\n**Placeholders to replace:**\n- `{{AIRTABLE_BASE_ID}}` → Airtable base ID\n- `{{BAS_TRACKER_SHEET_ID}}` → Google Sheet ID for BAS tracker\n\n**Airtable 'BAS Clients' table must have columns:** ClientName, ClientEmail, AccountantEmail, XeroTenantId, Active (checkbox), LodgementCycle\n\n⚠️ Xero Reports API requires `Xero-Tenant-Id` header per request — stored per client in Airtable.",
        "height": 440,
        "width": 780,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "sticky-04",
      "name": "Workflow Info",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        256,
        112
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "rule": {
          "interval": [
            {
              "field": "cronExpression",
              "expression": "0 7 1 1,4,7,10 *"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "id": "sched-04",
      "name": "Quarterly BAS Trigger",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.scheduleTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1.2,
      "position": [
        256,
        624
      ]
